# Task agent quality controls

When delegating work to Task (subagent) agents:

## Before delegating

- Give narrow, file-specific instructions. List exact files and exact patterns.
- Tell the agent what it must NOT do: no new files, no unrelated changes, no
  proactive refactoring beyond the stated scope.
- Prefer the default model for refactoring across many files. Only use `fast`
  for trivial, single-file tasks.

## After receiving results

- Always run `git diff --stat` and scan the output BEFORE staging.
- If new untracked files appear that were not requested, investigate before
  committing.
- Never use `git add -A` after Task agent work. Stage only the files that
  were part of the task specification.
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` after code changes spanning more than 3 files.
- Spot-check at least 2-3 files from the diff for correctness (ternary
  operators, removed branches, import cleanup).

## Known pitfalls

- Fast agents can duplicate values in ternary branches (`"zip" : "zip"`).
- Fast agents may create files unprompted (gateway-policy.ts, audit docs).
- Fast agents may remove too much or too little when cleaning up imports.
